The licensor grants you a patent license for the software that covers patent claims the licensor can license, or becomes able to license, that you would infringe by using the software.

Noncommercial Purposes
Noncommercial purposes are purposes other than directly generating revenue or other commercial advantage. For example, using the software for research, experiment, personal projects, or developing noncommercial applications is allowed. You may not use the software as part of a product, service, or other activity intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

Notice
You must ensure that anyone who gets a copy of any part of the software from you also gets a copy of these terms.

Excuse
If the licensor notifies you of noncompliance with any of these terms, you can keep your license by taking all practical steps to comply within 30 days after the notice. If you do not do so, your license ends immediately.

Patent Defense
If you make any written claim that the software infringes or contributes to infringement of any patent, your patent license for the software ends immediately. If your company makes such a claim, your patent license ends immediately for work on behalf of your company.

Copyright Defense
If you make any written claim that the software infringes or contributes to infringement of any copyright, your copyright license for the software ends immediately. If your company makes such a claim, your copyright license ends immediately for work on behalf of your company.

No Other Rights
These terms do not imply any licenses other than those expressly granted in these terms.

Termination
If your license ends, you must stop using the software and take reasonable steps to discontinue distributing it. However, your obligations under these terms continue. Those who received copies of the software from you before your license ended will keep their licenses.

